HEADWORD: Zimb
<hw>Zimb</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A
large, venomous, two-winged fly, native of Abyssinia. It is allied to
the tsetse fly, and, like the latter, is destructive to
cattle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

